main event: A civilian pilot flying over Devils Lake, North Dakota observed a string of lights on July 16, 1960.
interesting points: The sighting was reported by S/Sgt Rodrlques of the 735th Radar Sq (FINLEY AF STATION, Findlay North Dakota).
The pilot was part of the Civil Air Patrol flying over Devils Lake.
The sighting occurred at 0213 EST on July 17, 1960.
The report was extracted from Capt Bracke's Report dated July 16, 1960.
The report concludes that the sighting was possibly a balloon, but there was insufficient data for evaluation.
result: Possibly a Balloon, Insufficient Data for Evaluation
